		<div class="quote"><p>I think it's important that you mention our most important duty: to build web-pages (with or without Flash) in a thoughtful manner, so that HTML5 (et al) doesn't become what Flash is now.</p>
<p>Because, really, it doesn't matter if we get rid of Flash, if we just end up doing it all again with a different technology.</p>
<p>(Think: Canvas libraries that create the same 'skip intro' sites we saw with Flash, or, as you mentioned, ajax that doesn't allow deep-linking.)</p>
<p>We need to be warned, again and again, what can happen if we don't do our duty.
</p>
